1. Clone the repo in the ~/.vim folder:
git clone git@github.com:ruxandraburtica/vim.git ~/.vim

2. Update submodules
cd ~/.vim
git submodule init
git submodule update

3. Copy the .vimrc in the home directory

4. Command-T requires vim to be compiled with Ruby support, so:
sudo apt-get install ruby1.9.1-dev
sudo gem install sys-proctable
sudo gem install passenger

From ~/.vim/bundle/command-t, run:
rake make
